# Fish Shell Configuration
# Main config file - delegates to modular conf.d/ files
#
# Module Loading Order:
#   00-env.fish         - Environment variables
#   10-paths.fish       - PATH configuration
#   20-tools.fish       - Modern CLI tools (bat, eza, fzf, yazi)
#   30-git.fish         - Git abbreviations
#   40-abbreviations.fish - General abbreviations
#   50-functions.fish   - Custom helper functions
#   60-work.fish        - Work-specific configuration (conditional)
#   99-init.fish        - Shell initialization (zoxide, starship)
#
# Files in conf.d/ are loaded automatically by Fish in alphabetical order.
# The numbering (00-, 10-, etc.) ensures predictable load sequence.
#
# To add new configuration:
#   - Create new file in ~/.config/fish/conf.d/
#   - Use number prefix to control load order
#   - Restart shell or run: source ~/.config/fish/config.fish
#
# Backup of original config: ~/.config/fish/config.fish.backup
